<exercise checkit-seed="0038" checkit-slug="E3" checkit-title="Solving linear systems">
  <statement>
    <p>Show how to find the solution set for the following 
    
            system of linear equations.
            <md alignment="alignat" alignat-columns=" 5 "><mrow>-x_{1} &amp;-&amp; 4 \, x_{2} &amp;+&amp; x_{3} &amp;+&amp; x_{4} &amp;=&amp; -3</mrow><mrow>x_{1} &amp;+&amp; 4 \, x_{2} &amp;+&amp; 4 \, x_{3} &amp;-&amp; 6 \, x_{4} &amp;=&amp; -7</mrow><mrow>x_{1} &amp;+&amp; 4 \, x_{2} &amp;+&amp; x_{3} &amp;-&amp; 3 \, x_{4} &amp;=&amp; -1</mrow></md></p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>\mathrm{RREF} \left[\begin{array}{cccc|c}
-1 &amp; -4 &amp; 1 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 \\
1 &amp; 4 &amp; 4 &amp; -6 &amp; -7 \\
1 &amp; 4 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 &amp; -1
\end{array}\right]  =  \left[\begin{array}{cccc|c}
1 &amp; 4 &amp; 0 &amp; -2 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; -1 &amp; -2 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] </me>
    <p>The solution set is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
-4 \, a + 2 \, b + 1 \\
a \\
b - 2 \\
b
\end{array}\right] \middle|\,a\text{\texttt{,}}b\in\mathbb{R}\right\} </m></p>
  </answer>
</exercise>

